  "general": {
    "title": "About IMO",
    "content": "\n\n<dl class=\"condensed\">\n<dt><a href=\"advisory.aspx\">IMO board</a></dt>\n<dd>Members of the IMO Board</dd>\n<dt><a href=\"ethics.aspx\">Ethics Committee</a></dt>\n<dd>Members of the Ethics Committee</dd>\n<!--\n<dt><a href=\"regulations_2006.aspx\">Regulations</a></dt>\n<dd>Regulations)</dd>\n-->\n<dt><a href=\"documents.aspx\">Documents</a></dt>\n<dd>This is the page to access various documents related to IMO.</dd>\n<dt><a href=\"http://www.imof.co/\">IMO Foundation</a></dt>\n<dd>The IMO Foundation is a charity which supports the IMO.</dd>\n<dt><a href=\"forum_login.aspx\">IMO forum</a></dt>\n<dd>Available only for leaders of national teams <img alt=\"Locked\" src=\"/web/20251230193136im_/https://www.imo-official.org/App_Themes/lock_icon.gif\"/></dd>\n</dl>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The IMO logo was introduced in IMO 1995 in Canada. The IMO logo is available in several graphic formats. For publication (ie. press) one should use the logo in the CMYK color scheme.</p>\n\n\n<table>\n<thead><tr><th>Graphics formats</th><th>Files</th></tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td>CDR (CorelDraw)</td><td><a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_CMYK.cdr\">CMYK</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_RGB.cdr\">RGB</a></td></tr>\n<tr><td>AI (Adobe Illustrator)</td><td><a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_CMYK.ai\">CMYK</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_RGB.ai\">RGB</a></td></tr>\n<tr><td>EPS (PostScript 1)</td><td><a href=\"logo/IMOLogo.eps\">CMYK</a></td></tr>\n<tr><td>PDF</td><td><a href=\"logo/IMOLogo.pdf\">CMYK</a></td></tr>\n<tr><td>PNG</td><td><a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_30px.png\">30 × 21</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_70px.png\">70 × 48</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_100px.png\">100 × 69</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_200px.png\">200 × 138</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_300px.png\">300 × 206</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_400px.png\">400 × 275</a></td></tr>\n<tr><td>GIF</td><td><a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_30px.gif\">30 × 21</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_70px.gif\">70 × 48</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_100px.gif\">100 × 69</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_200px.gif\">200 × 138</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_300px.gif\">300 × 206</a>, <a href=\"logo/IMOLogo_400px.gif\">400 × 275</a></td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The official IMO flag was introduced at IMO 1995 in Canada along with the IMO logo. The flag is white with the IMO logo in its centre. It became a tradition that the IMO flag is passed to the next host at the end of the Closing Ceremony.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The IMO hymn was introduced at IMO 1997 in Argentina. \n    <a href=\"download_file.aspx?DLFile=IMO_Hymn.mp3\" id=\"ctl00_CPH_Main_HyperLink1\">Download MP3</a></p>\n\n\n<p>IMO 2016 donated music (composer: Dr Mui Kwong Chiu)\n    <a href=\"download_file.aspx?DLFile=IMO_Theme.mp3\" id=\"ctl00_CPH_Main_HyperLink2\">IMO Theme (mp3)</a>\n<a href=\"download_file.aspx?DLFile=IMO_Theme_Slow.mp3\" id=\"ctl00_CPH_Main_HyperLink3\">IMO Theme Slow (mp3)</a>\n<a href=\"documents/IMO_Theme_Tunes.pdf\">Tunes</a>\n<a href=\"documents/IMO_Theme_Lyrics.pdf\">Lyrics</a>\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>At the moment the IMO database contains information about 22337 contestants. The IMO server is hosted by the Faculty of Mathematics and Physics of the University of Ljubljana and maintained by <a href=\"mailto:webmaster@imo-official.org\">Matjaž Željko (webmaster)</a>.</p>\n\n"
  },
  "links": {
    "title": "Links and Resources",
    "content": "\n\n<dl class=\"normal\">\n<dt><a href=\"http://www.artofproblemsolving.com/\">Art of Problem Solving</a></dt>\n<dd>Problem solving resources (including IMO), on-line classes.</dd>\n<dt><a href=\"http://www.mathlinks.ro/Forum/portal.php\">Mathlinks</a></dt>\n<dd>Forums, huge community, lots of resources (including IMO).</dd>\n<!--\n<dt><a href=\"http://www.mathlinks.ro/index.php?f=456\">PEN</a></dt>\n<dd>Problems in Elementary Number Theory</dd>\n\n<dt><a href=\"http://www.imomath.com/\">The IMO compendium</a></dt>\n<dd>Problems from IMO and other mathematical competitions around the world.</dd>\n-->\n</dl>\n\n"
  },
  "advisory": {
    "title": "IMO board",
    "content": "\n\n<h3><a class=\"pointer\" href=\"advisory.aspx?year=2025\">◄</a> <a class=\"highlight\" href=\"year_info.aspx?year=2026\">67<sup>th</sup> IMO 2026</a> </h3>\n\n\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Gregor Dolinar\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage19996.jpg\" title=\"Gregor Dolinar\"/></div><p><b>Gregor Dolinar</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=SVN\">Slovenia</a>)</p><p>President</p></div>\n\n\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Ria van Huffel\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage19994.jpg\" title=\"Ria van Huffel\"/></div><p><b>Ria van Huffel</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=BEL\">Belgium</a>)</p><p>Secretary general</p></div>\n\n\n<h3>Elected members</h3>\n\n\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Dávid Kunszenti-Kovács\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage11433.jpg\" title=\"Dávid Kunszenti-Kovács\"/></div><p><b>Dávid Kunszenti-Kovács</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=NOR\">Norway</a>)</p><p> </p></div>\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Yongjin Song\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage9677.jpg\" title=\"Yongjin Song\"/></div><p><b>Yongjin Song</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=KOR\">Republic of Korea</a>)</p><p> </p></div>\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Géza Kós\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage19997.jpg\" title=\"Géza Kós\"/></div><p><b>Géza Kós</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=HUN\">Hungary</a>)</p><p> </p></div>\n\n\n<h3>Co-opted members<br/>\n<span style=\"font-size:small;\">(representing the host countries of immediate past, present and future two IMOs)</span>\n</h3>\n\n\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Ben Kirk\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage19998.jpg\" title=\"Ben Kirk\"/></div><p><b>Ben Kirk</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=AUS\">Australia</a>)</p><p><a href=\"year_info.aspx?year=2025\">IMO 2025</a></p></div>\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Liang Xiao\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage21025.jpg\" title=\"Liang Xiao\"/></div><p><b>Liang Xiao</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=CHN\">People's Republic of China</a>)</p><p><a href=\"year_info.aspx?year=2026\">IMO 2026</a></p></div>\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Géza Kós\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage19997.jpg\" title=\"Géza Kós\"/></div><p><b>Géza Kós</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=HUN\">Hungary</a>)</p><p><a href=\"year_info.aspx?year=2027\">IMO 2027</a></p></div>\n<div class=\"photo\"><div><img alt=\"Sultan Albarakati\" height=\"135\" src=\"/web/20251202051022im_/http://www.imo-official.org/photos/2026/ThumbImage19993.jpg\" title=\"Sultan Albarakati\"/></div><p><b>Sultan Albarakati</b><br/>(<a href=\"country_info.aspx?code=SAU\">Saudi Arabia</a>)</p><p><a href=\"year_info.aspx?year=2028\">IMO 2028</a></p></div>\n\n"
  },
